d Kingdom","England":"England","Plumpton, Yorkshire, England":"Plumpton by Ecclesall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Plumptom","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places called with Old English <i>plūme</i>, <i>plȳme</i> ‘plum, plum tree’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, including Plumpton (Yorkshire, Northamptonshire, Sussex, Cumbria), Fieldplumpton or Woodplumpton (Lancashire), Plympton (Devon), and a lost <i>Plumpton</i> in Kingsbury (Warwicks)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter I De Plumptom was born in 1133, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Eldredus Plumpton, was 26 and his mother, Petronilla de York, was 16. He married Helena De Plumptom about 1159, in Plumpton by Ecclesall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 5 sons and 1 daughter. He died in Plumpton by Ecclesall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1133–":"1133–Surnud","1133–Male":"1133–Surnud","1136–1187":"1136–1187","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1157–Male":"1157–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1163–Male":"1163–Surnud","1168–1214":"1168–1214","1184–Male":"1184–Surnud","1107–Male":"1107–Surnud","1117–Female":"1117–Surnud","1187":"1187","1163":"1163","1184":"1184","1160":"1160","1107":"1107","ABT 1184":"umbes 1184","1117":"1117","1214":"1214","circa 1163":"umbes 1163","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1168":"1168","1133":"1133","1155":"1155","about 1159":"umbes 1159","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Plumpton, Yorkshire, England":"Plumpton by Ecclesall, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1133–":"1133–Kuollut","1133–Male":"1133–Kuollut","1136–1187":"1136–1187","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1157–Male":"1157–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1163–Male":"1163–Kuollut","1168–1214":"1168–1214","1184–Male":"1184–Kuollut","1107–Male":"1107–Kuollut","1117–Female":"1117–Kuollut","1187":"1187","1163":"1163","1184":"1184","1160":"1160","1107":"1107","ABT 1184":"noin 1184","1117":"1117","1214":"1214","circa 1163":"noin 1163","1136":"1136","1157":"1157","1168":"1168","1133":"1133","1155":"1155","about 1159":"noin 1159","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Plumpton, Yorkshire, Eng